### 4. Farmer Onboarding Flow

#### [NEW] [src/flows/onboarding.ts](file:///Users/john/Desktop/projects/biochar/src/flows/onboarding.ts)

**One-time registration flow:**
1. Farmer sends first message → bot replies: *"Welcome to GG Krishi. Let's register your farm."*
2. Collect: **Name**, **Village**, **Aadhaar last 4** (optional), **UPI ID**
3. Prompt: *"Share your current location while standing in your field."*
4. Store GPS as farm center + default 500m radius
5. Reply: *"Registration complete! Scan your first biochar bag QR to begin."*

**Linkage created:** `Phone → Farmer Identity → Farm GPS Boundary`

---

### 5. QR Bag Linking System

#### [NEW] [src/flows/bagLinking.ts](file:///Users/john/Desktop/projects/biochar/src/flows/bagLinking.ts)

Each physical biochar bag has a QR code that opens:
```
https://wa.me/91XXXXXXXXXX?text=GG-P1-2026-02-B10291
```

**Flow:**
1. Farmer scans QR → WhatsApp opens with pre-filled bag ID
2. Backend validates: bag exists, bag not already claimed
3. Mark: `bag.status = "CLAIMED"`, `bag.claimedByFarmerId = farmer.id`
4. Reply: *"Bag #10291 linked! Now share your location and take a photo to verify application."*

**Anti-duplicate:** Bag ID can only be claimed once. Second scan → `"This bag has already been claimed."`

---

### 6. GPS + Camera Verification Endpoint

#### [NEW] [src/flows/verification.ts](file:///Users/john/Desktop/projects/biochar/src/flows/verification.ts)
#### [NEW] [src/camera/index.html](file:///Users/john/Desktop/projects/biochar/src/camera/index.html)

**Two-step verification:**

**Step A — Location capture:**
- Farmer shares WhatsApp live location
- Backend checks: is GPS within registered farm boundary?
- Uses Haversine formula: `distance(farmerGPS, farmCenter) <= farmRadius`
- If outside → reject: *"Location doesn't match your registered farm."*

**Step B — Camera capture (In-App Browser):**
- Bot sends link: `https://verify.ggkrishi.com/capture?farmerId=X&bagId=Y`
- WebView captures:
  - Camera image (direct capture, no gallery)
  - Browser GPS at capture time
  - Timestamp
  - Device user-agent
- Uploads to backend → stored in S3
- SHA-256 hash computed and stored

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Normal WhatsApp photos **strip EXIF metadata**. The in-app browser WebView approach preserves GPS + timestamp at capture time — this is critical for audit integrity.

