### 10. Blockchain Hash Anchoring (Optional — Phase 3)

#### [NEW] [src/blockchain/anchor.ts](file:///Users/john/Desktop/projects/biochar/src/blockchain/anchor.ts)

**Purpose:** Prove audit logs haven't been tampered with after storage.

**How it works:**
1. Daily batch: collect all verification records from past 24h
2. Compute Merkle root hash of all records
3. Write hash to Polygon smart contract
4. Store `txHash` in each verification record

**Smart contract (Solidity):**
```solidity
contract AuditAnchor {
    mapping(uint256 => bytes32) public dailyHashes;
    
    event HashAnchored(uint256 indexed day, bytes32 hash);
    
    function anchor(uint256 day, bytes32 hash) external onlyOwner {
        require(dailyHashes[day] == 0, "Already anchored");
        dailyHashes[day] = hash;
        emit HashAnchored(day, hash);
    }
}
```

**Cost:** ~$0.01 per daily anchor on Polygon.

> [!NOTE]
> Blockchain does **NOT** prevent fraud. It only proves data wasn't altered after recording. All fraud prevention happens off-chain in the AI + Fraud Engine layers.

